Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Flights
There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Antigua and Barbuda as all international airlines with direct or connecting flights to the UK have suspended operations. Regional airline LIAT has suspended all operations from 4 – 18 April.
We know this is concerning for British people trying to leave Antigua and Barbuda. The UK government is working closely with airlines, the Antigua and Barbuda authorities and other governments to make sure options are available for you to return to the UK as soon as possible.
What to do
If you cannot leave Antigua and Barbuda at this time, you should:
follow the advice of local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus. The Government of Antigua and Barbuda post updates via Facebook, Instagram and Twitter
find accommodation that’s suitable for your needs
keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well
Future travel options
The UK government is working closely with airlines, the Antigua and Barbuda authorities and other governments to make sure options are available for you to return to the UK as soon as possible. This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission on Twitter, Facebook, or Instagram.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British High Commission in Bridgetown on + 1 246 430 7800.
The High Commission cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts.
Further information
See additional advice on what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
